<HEADLINE>
<P>
'DRUG-DEAL VICTIM' KIDNAPS WOMAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 23-year-old East San Diego woman was kidnaped Wednesday afternoon near San 
Diego State University and, with a gun pointed at her head, was ordered to 
drive for almost an hour by a man who claimed to have been victimized by "a 
drug deal gone bad" and needed to find his car, police said. 
</P>
<P>
The woman told San Diego police she was walking from campus to her car in the 
5500 block of Hardy Avenue when a man walked up, wielding a semiautomatic 
handgun. 
</P>
<P>
The man said, "Get in the car or I'll kill you," the woman told police. 
</P>
<P>
She said she followed the man's "continuous and disorganized directions" until 
he ordered her to pull over at Jamacha Road and Gustavo Street in El Cajon. 
After a brief struggle, police said, the man headed north on Jamacha on foot. 
</P>
<P>
He was wearing a blue baseball cap, blue jacket, brown pants and red tennis 
shoes, police said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
