<HEADLINE>
<P>
3-A SOCCER SEMIFINALS; 
</P>
<P>
TORREY PINES KEEPS SURPRISING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Layla Massiroughli scored on a direct free kick from 23 yards with 12 minutes 
remaining to wake Torrey Pines from its first-half slumber and give the Falcons 
a 1-0 victory over Bonita Vista Wednesday in the 3-A girls' soccer semifinal 
match at San Diego High. 
</P>
<P>
"It was like we took the first half off," Torrey Pines Coach Dennis Costello 
said. 
</P>
<P>
Torrey Pines (16-4-2) surprised Costello this season, winning consistently with 
only three senior starters. The Falcons have three consecutive shutouts in the 
playoffs. 
</P>
<P>
In the other 3-A girls' semifinal: 
</P>
<P>
Poway 1, San Dieguito 0 -- Poway advanced to meet Torrey Pines, the defending 
champions, Saturday at 7:30 p.m. at Torrey Pines. 
</P>
<P>
In the 3-A boys' semifinal games: 
</P>
<P>
Bonita Vista 2, Poway 1 -- Bonita Vista (20-3-1) advanced to a 3-A championship 
meeting with Monte Vista Saturday at 5:30 at Torrey Pines. 
</P>
<P>
Monte Vista 2, Sweetwater 0 -- Ernie Reyes scored both goals to lead Monte 
Vista (16-5-3). Sweetwater finished 13-4-2. 
</P>
