<P>
HEALTH, ENERGY SECRETARIES WIN SENATE CONFIRMATION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From United Press International 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
WASHINGTON 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Senate on Wednesday overwhelmingly confirmed Louis W. Sullivan as health 
and human services secretary and James D. Watkins as energy secretary. In 
back-to-back ballots, senators voted 98 to 1 for Sullivan, a physician who was 
the only black nominated for a Cabinet post, and 99 to 0 for Watkins, a retired 
admiral who led former President Ronald Reagan's AIDS commission. 
</P>
<P>
Sen. Jesse Helms (R-N. C.) cast the vote against Sullivan. He charged that the 
head of Atlanta's Morehouse College medical school had ducked questions about 
issues such as fetal research and AIDS confidentiality. 
</P>
