<P>
Cipher Data to Buy Firm: San Diego-based Cipher Data has signed a definitive 
agreement to pay $76.7 million for Irwin Magnetic Systems Inc., an Ann Arbor, 
Mich., manufacturer of computer data-storage products, Cipher Chairman Gary E. 
Liebl said. Irwin reported a $1.6-million net profit and $49 million in revenue 
for the most recent fiscal year. Cipher, which was granted options for 15% of 
Irwin's outstanding shares, will initiate a $13-per-share cash tender offer for 
Irwin's 5.9 million shares. 
</P>
