<P>
New Technology Developed: Nippon Telegraph &amp; Telephone Corp. said it has 
produced the world's smallest radio receiver, which will pave the way for 
production of super-miniature mobile telephones. Japan's giant domestic 
telecommunications company said the production of the 26 gigahertz receiver was 
made possible by the firm's development of a new uniplanar circuit 
configuration for monolithic-microwave integrated circuit, or MMIC. The firm 
said the uniplanar MMIC can help reduce cost and size and improve reliability 
of super-high-frequency equipment. 
</P>
