<P>
Pepsi's Hot Spot: Just about anyone watching commercial television tonight -- 
almost anywhere in the world -- has a good chance of viewing the much 
ballyhooed Pepsi-Cola commercial featuring rock star Madonna. The two-minute 
ad, which ad industry sources estimate cost Pepsi more than $1 million to 
create and upwards of $5 million to air, will be shown in 40 countries. The ad, 
which features Madonna debuting her new song "Like a Prayer," will be aired in 
the United States during the first commercial break of "The Cosby Show" on NBC. 
Later in the evening, 30-second versions of the ad will air during the TV shows 
"Cheers" and "LA Law." 
</P>
