<P>
GAF Trial to Continue: The federal judge hearing the stock manipulation case 
against GAF Corp. and its vice chairman denied their motion to dismiss the 
case. GAF and James Sherwin requested the dismissal after the government 
concluded its arguments Tuesday. But U.S. District Judge Mary Johnson Lowe said 
the government had presented sufficient evidence for the case to continue. The 
government has charged GAF, a specialty chemical company, and Sherwin with 
attempting to boost the price of Union Carbide shares in 1986. 
