<P>
PEOPLE: 3 EX-OFFICERS OF SALOMON TO START INVESTMENT FIRM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Three former senior executives of the Salomon Bros. financial firm, William J. 
Voute, E. Craig Coats Jr. and Ronald M. Stuart, announced the formation of a 
new investment firm, Voute Coats Stuart &amp; O'Grady L.P. 
</P>
<P>
Voute, 50, will be chairman and chief executive. Coats and Stuart, both 41, 
will be vice chairmen. The firm is headquartered in Greenwich, Conn. 
</P>
<P>
Voute, a former vice chairman of Salomon Bros., as well as a director of its 
parent company, Salomon Inc., is a 30-year veteran of the securities industry. 
</P>
