<HEADLINE>
<P>
ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
FULLERTON DEFEATS SADDLEBACK IN ORANGE EMPIRE SOFTBALL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Kristin Jacobs pitched a three-hitter as Fullerton College's softball team 
defeated Saddleback, 1-0, Wednesday in the Orange Empire Conference opener for 
both schools at Fullerton. 
</P>
<P>
Jacobs (8-4) struck out nine and didn't walk a batter. 
</P>
<P>
Tammy Rodriguez led off the ninth with an infield single. She went to second on 
a passed ball and was sacrificed to third. 
</P>
<P>
Rodriguez then scored on a squeeze bunt by Kelly Hilliard. 
</P>
<P>
In other Orange Empire Conference play: 
</P>
<P>
Rancho Santiago 7, Orange Coast 1 -- Natalie Sanchez threw a two-hitter for 
Rancho Santiago (8-5, 1-0) at Orange. Sanchez (8-4) struck out two and walked 
one. She allowed only a fifth-inning run. The Dons took the lead in the third 
with three runs. Kim Wolf had a two-run single in the inning. Heather Illsley 
had two hits and scored three runs and Judy Padialla had three hits and one RBI 
for the Dons. 
</P>
<P>
Golden West 2, Riverside 0 -- Golden West scored single runs in the second and 
the seventh at Riverside. Tammie Flores (3-3) gave up only two hits for Golden 
West (7-4 overall, 1-0 in conference). Riverside is 0-1 in conference. 
</P>
<P>
In Orange Empire Conference women's swimming: 
</P>
<P>
Cypress 80, Saddleback 50 -- Sami Teofilo and Laurel Strother each won two 
events to lead the Chargers (2-0 in conference) at home. Teofilo won the 
100-yard freestyle in 57.65 seconds and the 200 freestyle in 2:03.39. Strother 
won the 50 backstroke in 33.40 and 100 backstroke in 1:12.46. Saddleback is 1-1 
in conference play. 
</P>
</TEXT>
