<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN GABRIEL VALLEY DIGEST: ALHAMBRA; 
</P>
<P>
OPPOSITION TO DRUG CENTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The City Council voted 5 to 0 Monday to oppose plans by a private health 
service firm to locate a methadone maintenance and detoxification center near 
residential neighborhoods in Alhambra. 
</P>
<P>
The methadone treatment center, proposed for a site at 5401 Valley Blvd. in Los 
Angeles by Altamed Health Services Corp., would be 3/10 of a mile west of 
Alhambra's city limit. 
</P>
<P>
Up to 300 heroin addicts a day may seek treatment at the center, according to a 
memorandum written by Police Chief Russ Siverling. 
</P>
</TEXT>
