<HEADLINE>
<P>
CHARITY SCOREBOARD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
"An Affair of the Heart" dinner Feb. 15 at the Four Seasons Hotel in Newport 
Beach netted about $25,000 for the Heart Institute of Saddleback Hospital &amp; 
Health Center. Nan Owen was chairwoman. 
</P>
<P>
The Orange County Law Auxiliary's "Mardi Gras Matinee" fashion show Feb. 18 at 
the Irvine Hilton &amp; Towers netted about $6,000 for Victim-Witness Assn., 
Orange County Sexual Assault Network and Shortstop, a juvenile delinquency 
diversion program. Donna Saltarelli was chairwoman. 
</P>
<P>
The "First Ladies on Parade: Inaugural Gowns" luncheon and fashion show Friday 
at the Anaheim Hilton &amp; Towers netted about $10,000 for the county chapter 
of Freedoms Foundation. Carole Engstrom was chairwoman. 
</P>
<P>
The "Ambassador of Life" recognition dinner Saturday at the Anaheim Marriott 
netted about $25,000 for the American Cancer Society's county unit. Dixie 
Bullington was chairwoman. 
</P>
<P>
The "Nordstrom Spring Trend Show" on Saturday at Nordstrom South Coast Plaza, 
Costa Mesa, netted about $5,000 for KOCE-TV, Channel 50, of Huntington Beach. 
Jo Caines was chairwoman. 
</P>
<P>
The dinner-dance on Saturday at the Irvine Hilton &amp; Towers netted about 
$83,000 for Tri-County chapter of the Leukemia Society of America. Kevin Spence 
and Peter DiMicelli were co-chairmen. 
</P>
<P>
"A Caribbean Night With Jean-Michel Cousteau" on Saturday at the Balboa Bay 
Club netted about $10,000 for the Handicapped Scuba Assn. Patricia Derk Gatacre 
was chairwoman. 
</P>
<P>
"Wine Fest '89" on Sunday at the Anaheim Marriott netted about $15,000 for the 
Town &amp; Country Committee of the Orange County Philharmonic Society. Marcia 
Harris was chairwoman. 
</P>
</TEXT>
