<P>
WOODLAND HILLS CRASH KILLS WOMAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times staff and wire service reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A motorist was killed and two others were injured today in Woodland Hills when 
a car making a turn on rain-slick streets and an oncoming Jeep collided, Los 
Angeles police said. 
</P>
<P>
The identities of the woman killed and the two men injured in the 8 a.m. 
accident on Topanga Canyon Boulevard at Erwin Street were not released. 
</P>
<P>
Sgt. Joe Cross said a car with a man and woman in it was heading southbound on 
Topanga Canyon Boulevard and attempted to turn left on to Erwin Street. The 
driver of the northbound Jeep was unable to stop and the two vehicles collided. 
</P>
<P>
The woman, who was a passenger in the car, died at the scene of the accident. 
The driver was hospitalized with unknown injuries while the driver of the Jeep 
was treated for minor injuries at the scene. 
