<P>
BUSH TELLS DOUBTS ON CONTRA PACT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times staff and wire service reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
WASHINGTON 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
President Bush voiced doubts in talks today with Guatemala's president about 
the recent Central American peace agreement that would disband the Contra 
forces as he mulls over keeping them alive with U.S. aid, Bush's spokesman 
said. 
