<TEXT>
<P>
Illegal immigrants are being housed in tents after the dormitories at a 
southern Texas detention center filled up with rejected applicants for 
political asylum, an immigration official said today. 
</P>
<P>
Twenty-eight men slept in a tent Tuesday night, after the Immigration and 
Naturalization Service ran out of bed space for male detainees in buildings at 
the minimum-security center here, INS spokeswoman Virginia Kice said. "This is 
the first time the tents have been deployed," Kice said. "We've reached our 
capacity." The INS has been faced with a flood of Central Americans it 
maintains are filing "frivolous" applications for political asylum after 
illegally crossing the Rio Grande into southern Texas. 
